components.name: Fetch Brokerage Holdings
components.description: Retrieves mock holdings CSV data for a given brokerage account via a simulated API call.
outputs: holdings_data (dictionary with brokerage ID and holdings list)

components.name: Analyze Portfolio
components.description: Calculates portfolio metrics such as total value, allocation percentages, and risk score for each brokerage's holdings.

upstream_policy.description: Runs after its corresponding fetch_brokerage_holdings task completes successfully

components.name: Aggregate and Rebalance
components.description: Aggregates portfolio analysis results from all brokerages and computes the set of rebalancing trades needed to meet target allocations.
inputs: analysis_results (list of dictionaries from all analyze_portfolio tasks)

upstream_policy.description: Executes after all analyze_portfolio tasks have succeeded

components.name: Generate Trade Orders
components.description: Creates a timestamped CSV file containing the final trade orders derived from the rebalancing calculation.

description.description: Human readable description of the pipeline

batch_window.description: Batch window parameter name (e.g., ds, execution_date)

partitioning.description: Data partitioning strategy (e.g., daily, hourly, monthly)

depends_on_past.description: Whether execution depends on previous run success

brokerage_id.description: Identifier of the brokerage account to fetch holdings from

holdings_data.description: Holdings data dictionary received from fetch task

analysis_results.description: List of analysis result dictionaries from all brokerages

rebalancing_trades.description: List of trade dictionaries generated by aggregation

sources: Mock brokerage API providing holdings CSV data for each brokerage account (BROKERAGE_001005)
sinks: Timestamped CSV file (trade_orders_YYYYMMDD.csv) containing the final rebalancing trade orders
